Run the ATRC workflow

Source: R/atrc_workflow.R
run_workflow.Rd

This workflow creates a synthetic population from a reference sample and control data as specified in the input config file. The fitting and replicating algorithms can also be selected in the config file.

Usage

run_workflow(config_path = "/atrc_data/parameters.yaml")

Arguments

config_path

path to an ATRC workflow config file. See the Details section below for the expected format.

Value

a list of mlfit's fitted problem and a data.frame

of the resulting synthetic population.

Details

Here is the expected format of a config file.

inputs:
  REFERENCE_SAMPLE:
    type: path
    path: /atrc_data/inputs/reference_sample.csv
  PERSONS_CONTROL:
    type: multiple_paths
    path:
      - /atrc_data/inputs/persons-control1.csv
  HOUSEHOLDS_CONTROL:
    type: multiple_paths
    path:
      - /atrc_data/inputs/households-control1.csv
  GROUP_ID:
    type: value
    value: "hhid"
  INDIVIDUAL_ID:
    type: value
    value: "persid"
  COUNT:
    type: value
    value: "n"
  ML_FIT_ALGORITHM:
    type: value
    value: "ipu"
  ML_REPLICATE_ALGORITHM:
    type: value
    value: "trs"
outputs:
  SYNTHETIC_POPULATION:
    type: csv
    path: /atrc_data/outputs/synthetic_population.csv
